In a large skillet over medium-high heat, melt the lard. Add the onion, bell pepper and garlic; saute for 2 minutes, stirring frequently. Add the corn kernels and cook 10 minutes, stirring occasionally. Add water, potatoes and pumpkin. Whisk in the tomato paste. Season to taste with salt and pepper. Lower heat and simmer for 1 hour or until the potatoes are tender. Ladle the soup into bowls and serve.